cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.DB 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the accuracy of digital forensic investigations, which is a crucial aspect of cybersecurity. It could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a method for measuring accuracy using information retrieval techniques. Additionally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a likely sub-category as the proposed method involves the use of precision and recall values commonly used in information retrieval. The paper also discusses the use of automated analysis tools, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper deals with the categorization of evidential objects, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DB (Databases).
